<item>
            <title>[LU-10098] Lustre resource agent can mis-identify resource mounts</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10098</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;tt&gt;Lustre&lt;/tt&gt; resource agent &lt;tt&gt;lustre_is_mounted()&lt;/tt&gt; greps the mountpoint from &lt;tt&gt;/proc/mounts&lt;/tt&gt; but if that mountpoint matches a substring of a different mountpoint&lt;br/&gt;
e.g. /mnt/ost1 and /mnt/ost11.&lt;br/&gt;
It will register as already mounted and fail to start.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
